data.title: News and Tribune
data.meta_description: News and Tribune - a place for remembering loved ones; a space for sharing memories, life stories, milestones, to express condolences, and celebrate life of your loved ones
data.text:
Estes Densford, Jr.

Estes William "Bill" Densford Jr. 81, New Albany, IN passed away at home on August 11, 2024.

He was born on February 18, 1943 in Scottsburg, IN to the late Estes William Densford Sr. and Onita (McKee) Densford. Bill worked for Public Service Indiana that went on to become Duke Energy and retired as a supervisor...

Dorothy Harris

Dorothy "Dottie" Harris, 93, passed away peacefully on August 10, 2024, in her home surrounded by family.

Lee Reid

Lee Thomas Reid, 64, of Indianapolis, IN passed away on August 6, 2024. Lee was born December 25, 1959, in Whitesville, KY to Earl S. Reid and Ferdie (Kelley) Reid.

Lee was a proud graduate of Clarksville High School where he formed many lifelong friendships.

He went on to earn his degree from Indiana University...

Sonny Newton

My darling husband, Sonny Newton, 81, passed away in the early hours of Tuesday, August 6, 2024 at his home in Jeffersonville, IN. He was born on January 18, 1943 to the late Virgil Wilson Newton Sr. and Rosalind (Moss) Newton in Lexington, KY where the Wildcats are.

Sonny worked for 40 years as an operator with...

Aileen Rogge

Aileen Stepp Rogge passed away on August 5, 2024, surrounded by the love of her family at her home.

Doloris Tilly

Doloris M. Tilly, 80, of Floyds Knobs, IN passed away on Sunday, August 4, 2024.

She was born in Jeffersonville on September 22, 1943 to Doit and Dorothy (Faulkenburg) Myler.

Doloris was a member of Bethany Union Church, and a co-founder of the Chicken & Dumplings. She was active with the Hobart Beach VFW Post 1693,...

Marilyn Hammack

Marilyn Joyce Hammack, 67, died August 3, 2024.

Funeral service at 11 a.m. Tuesday, August 13, 2024, at Beanblossom-Cesar Funeral Home in Corydon. Visitation from 11 a.m. - 8 p.m. Monday and after 9 a.m. Tuesday at the funeral home.

John Herfel

John D. Herfel, 75, of Louisville, passed away Sunday, August 4, 2024.

John was born on June 9, 1949 in Jeffersonville, IN to Frank and Margaret Herfel.

Clyde Staley

Memorial visitation for Clyde Allen Staley, Sunday, August 11, from 1 p.m. to 3 p.m., Chapman Funeral Home, 431 West Harrison Avenue, Clarksville. Memorial service at 3 p.m. Sunday.

James Ross

Funeral Mass: Wednesday, July 24, 2024, at 11:00 a.m. at O.L.P.H. Church. Burial: Queen of Heaven Cemetery. Visitation:Tuesday, July 23, 2024, from 4-8:00 p.m. at E.M. Coots' Sons Funeral Home.

Carl Thien Jr.

Visitation for Carl Herman Thien Jr., 4-8 Monday, July 15 and 10 a.m.-noon Tuesday, July 16, Kraft Funeral Service, 2776 Charlestown Road. Funeral, noon Tuesday, at the funeral home.
